            <h4>City of Santa Rosa’s Must Do List
            </h4><ol><li>1. Acquaint yourself with the City by taking a walking tour in the City proper, where the old and the new converge. In the City proper, visitors are welcomed by the Santa Rosa Arch that leads to the modern and visitor-friendly City Hall. Fronting the City Hall is the City Plaza where one can take a trip down memory lane by visiting the newly-refurbished Museo de Santa Rosa, the Santa Rosa de Lima Parish Church, and some of the well-preserved Hispanic ancestral homes in the City Square.
                </li><li>2. Relax with some of the amenities the city has to offer. Bring your family and enjoy the rides at Enchanted Kingdom. Relax and unwind at the 18-hole golf course of world-class Santa Elena Golf and Country Club. Spend nightlife with friends and colleagues at Paseo de Santa Rosa where food is great and music is at its best.
                </li><li>3. Indulge yourself in many shopping malls spread around the City.
                </li><li>4. Stay in one of the City’s best hotels like the Paseo Premier Hotel, the Laguna Technopark Hotel or El Cielito Inn. Relax in some of the best resorts like the Southpick Resort and Rosalinda’s Garden.
                </li><li>5. Eat in one or two of the 199 restaurants and foodshops in the City. From local kitchenettes to fine-dining restaurants, the city boasts of a wide-range of variety.
                </li></ol><h3>Profile</h3>
            <p>Official Name: City of Santa Rosa</p> <p>Population: 266, 943</p>
            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>The City of Sta. Rosa is 40 kilometers south of Metro Manila and just 40 minutes away from Makati City. It is one and a half hours from the Ninoy Aquino International Airport.
                Depending on where one wants to go, the City of Santa Rosa is accessible via the South Luzon Expressway through three exits –Greenfield City (Mamplasan), Santa Rosa, and Eton City. The Balibago Complex is the City’s central transport terminal where one rides to go to their destination in and out of the City.
